# DSAR-OpenEnv: Complete Project Walkthrough

## What This Project Is

This is a **reinforcement learning environment** that simulates GDPR Data Subject Access Request (DSAR) compliance processing. It's built on Meta's [OpenEnv](https://github.com/meta-pytorch/OpenEnv) framework for the OpenEnv Hackathon 2026.

### The Real-World Problem

When a person writes to a company saying *"Give me all the data you have on me"* — that's a DSAR. Under GDPR (Article 15), the company has **30 days** to respond. They must:

1. **Disclose** all personal data they hold about that person
2. **Withhold** all internal business data (risk scores, churn models, internal notes)
3. **Not leak** sensitive operational data alongside the personal data

The catch: in real companies, personal data and internal data sit **mixed together** in the same databases. A CRM record for "Sarah Mitchell" contains her email (personal, must disclose) right next to her customer_health_score of 78.4 (internal, must withhold).

Today, compliance teams do this **manually** at ~$1,500 per request, with volumes growing 43% year-over-year.

